   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "766b0cd7-a343-4542-89dd-10f284c42b4e",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# What is Data Analysis?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "e3451ac8-f988-442b-9b85-d465f7c5c5e4",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Data Analysis is a process of inspecting, cleansing, transforming, and modeling data with the goal of discovering useful information, informing conclusion and supporting decision-making."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "9a9625f7-0df7-483a-a0d5-ddbdc60ee904",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Data Analysis Process"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "11549d82-fed6-4b5d-aae3-bf91c92f58cf",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Steps of Data Analysis Process-\n",
    "    1. Asking Questions\n",
    "    2. Data Wrangling \n",
    "    3. Exploratory Data Analysis(EDA)\n",
    "    4. Drawing Conclusions\n",
    "    5. Communicating Results/Data Storytelling"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "d29c1b44-3d3e-4ff0-a24f-24dabd702ee1",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Asking Questions:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "76e8b18d-df65-4f21-bdd6-f87a853f8950",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "There would be 2 Scenario's:\n",
    "    1. Data is Given with the questions, means what to do with the data.\n",
    "    2. Data is given without the Questions means you dont know what to do with the data\n",
    "\n",
    "In Second Scenario you have to ask the proper questions.\n",
    "\n",
    "Questions Would be like :\n",
    "    1. What features will contribute to my analysis?\n",
    "    2. What features are not important to my analysis?\n",
    "    3. Which of the features have strong correlation?\n",
    "    4. Do I need Data Processing?\n",
    "    5. What Type of feature Manipulation/Engineering is required?\n",
    "\n",
    "How can I  ask better Questions?\n",
    "    1. Subject Matter Expertise\n",
    "        - Subject Matter Expertise means the having knowledge about the subject means if the data is of IPL you should know about the cricket, if the data is about the any company you should know about the company and work of company.\n",
    "\n",
    "    2. Experience\n",
    "        - When you do things again and again then you get expertise in the subject this helps in asking the better questions.\n",
    "\n",
    "\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "a70c91fa-85f5-474f-98fb-cd8dfdcf285b",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Data Wrangling"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "f7fb837b-fc6e-4d98-a670-ac851af70dab",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Data Wrangling is also reffered to as data munging, is the Process of transforming and mapping data from one \"raw\" data form into another format with the intent of making it more appropriate and valuable for a variety of downstream purposes such as analytics.\n",
    "\n",
    "When the Data is in raw form which is not suitable/valid for analysis is cleaned by performing some operations on it and manipulated is called the Data Wrangling.\n",
    "\n",
    "Steps for Data Wrangling:\n",
    "    1. Data Gathering\n",
    "    2. Assessing the Data\n",
    "    3. Cleaning Data\n",
    "\n",
    "1. Data Gathering:\n",
    "    - Gathering Data From CSV File\n",
    "    - Gathering Data From API\n",
    "    - Gathering Data Using WEB SCRAPPING\n",
    "    - Gathering Data From DATABASES\n",
    "\n",
    "2. Data Assessing:\n",
    "    - Finding the number of Rows/Columns(Shape)\n",
    "    - Data Types of various columns (info())\n",
    "    - Checking for Missing values (info())\n",
    "    - Memory occupied by the dataset (info())\n",
    "    - High level mathematical overview of Data (describe())\n",
    "\n",
    "3. Cleaning Data\n",
    "    - This is Done if the Data is missing, Data is Duplicated, And Data having the Inorrect data type\n",
    "\n",
    "    - Missing Data is replaced by the mean/meadian or by other value\n",
    "    - Duplicated Data is Removed (drop_duplicates)\n",
    "    - Incorrect data type is corrected eg., Date having string data type which have to convert into datetime\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "fc12dea7-1099-4440-8d85-bf7653ba3248",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Exploratory Data Analysis(EDA)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "531d2954-7bf8-452f-9348-0e898c9bb100",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "There are 2 steps in EDA\n",
    "    1. Explore Data \n",
    "    2. Augment Data\n",
    "\n",
    "1. Exploring Data \n",
    "    - Finding Correlation and Covariance\n",
    "    - Doing univariate and multivariate analysis\n",
    "    - Plotting the graphs(data visualization)\n",
    "2. Augmenting Data\n",
    "    - there are  multiple things in Augmenting data some of them are,\n",
    "        - Removing outliers\n",
    "        - Merging of Dataframes if data is present in multiple dataframes\n",
    "        - Adding new column in Data\n",
    "    - Augmenting of Data is also called as Feature Engineering."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "88c33433-0ce0-4ba4-bbd0-3d407d36f090",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Drawing Conclusion"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "32a6e4c4-2a8f-4528-9020-1697cbc1b467",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We have to draw conclusion or predict the result based on analysis of data.\n",
    "- In terms of Data Science\n",
    "    - we use Machine learning to predict the result\n",
    "    - we use Inferential Statistics to predict the result\n",
    "- In terms of Data Analytics\n",
    "    - we use Descriptive Statistics\n",
    "\n",
    "Some example conclusions based on Descriptive Statistics:\n",
    "    1. Is Rohit Sharma a better batsman in second inning (IPL Dataset)?\n",
    "    2. Does being a Female increase your chances of survival (Titanic Dataset)?\n",
    "    3. Is Delhi the Most costly place for eating out (Zomato Dataset)?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "b26efef5-b35e-45cb-ae59-b36f895f30af",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. Communicating the Results/Data Storytelling"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "a418b14f-fced-467f-9bbf-83d6e8fe30ee",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "At last we have to communicate with the team or coleagues about the results of analysis.\n",
    "we have to make report, ppt, Blog post.\n",
    "we have to give the presentation on analysis results."
   ]
  }
 ],
